\appendix
\section{Reproduction Commands}
% ==================================================================

The main computational results can be reproduced with the following commands:

\begin{verbatim}
git clone https://github.com/Alpha-Stochastic-Research/asr-theory-of-speculation.git
cd asr-theory-of-speculation

python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

pytest -q

python src/brownian_motion.py
python src/option_pricing.py
\end{verbatim}

On Windows, the virtual environment can be activated with:

\begin{verbatim}
.venv\Scripts\activate
\end{verbatim}

The generated figures are saved in:

\begin{verbatim}
figures/
\end{verbatim}

